Updated Code Example
JavaScript
"use client";

import React from "react";
import Snowfall from "react-snowfall";

export default function SnowfallClient() {
  return (
    <Snowfall
      // A soft, icy blue color
      color="#dee4fd"
      // Applied as a fixed overlay so it covers the whole viewport
      style={{
        position: 'fixed',
        width: '100vw',
        height: '100vh',
        zIndex: 1000,
        pointerEvents: 'none', // Allows clicking through the snow to buttons/links
      }}
      // Controls the density
      snowflakeCount={400}
      // Optional: Adjusting size and speed for realism
      radius={[0.5, 3.0]}
      speed={[0.5, 2.0]}
      wind={[-0.5, 2.0]}
    />
  );
}
Key Props to Play With
Prop	Description
radius	An array [min, max] for snowflake size. Larger flakes look closer to the "camera."
speed	An array [min, max] for how fast the snow falls.
wind	An array [min, max] for horizontal movement.
images	You can actually pass an array of HTMLImageElement objects if you want to use custom flake shapes (like tiny stars or actual snowflake icons).
