Ahhh, I see what you mean — basically you’re thinking of copying the compiled HTML/JS from the browser dev tools instead of the source code. 😅

You can do it, but here’s the catch:

Why it’s tricky



What you get from DevTools is already compiled/minified code:

React components will be bundled JS, not JSX.



All imports (import X from "Y") are gone — replaced by long internal variable names.



Hard to edit or reuse:

You can’t just paste it into a new project and expect it to work.



Styling may break if Tailwind classes or images are compiled differently.



No easy access to original component structure:

All your reusable React components will appear as one blob of JS.

✅ Better alternatives

Use the source repo or ZIP download — gives you real JSX, separate files, and easy editing.



If you only want the visual layout:

Copy HTML + CSS from the browser.



But you’ll need to rebuild React logic manually.

💡 Quick rule: DevTools copy is good for inspiration or static snapshot, not for reusing a React project.

